  "commentary": "With SPX at 6576 sitting between the massive negative gamma wall at 6500 (-4694M) and positive gamma at 6605 (+1291M), dealers are currently in mixed hedging mode but the breakout regime dominates - they'll amplify any directional move away from this narrow band. The gex_surge event combined with -86.7% five-minute GEX change suggests rapid position adjustments are creating unstable hedging flows right here. Key inflection points are the 6500 level where dealers become aggressive buyers on any test, and 6605 where they flip to sellers - expect violent reactions at both strikes given the concentrated gamma.\n\nBottom line: price is trapped in a narrow explosive zone between 6500-6605 where any break triggers big dealer-driven moves.",
